definitions.definition: Something that is slightly different from a type or norm .
examples: All breeds of dog are variants of the species “Canis lupus familiaris”.

definitions.definition: A different sequence of a gene ( locus ).
A variable that can hold any of various unrelated data types .
One of a set of words or other linguistic forms that conveys the same meaning or serves the same function.
examples: The word "kerosine" is a variant of “kerosene”.

main_definition: Something that is slightly different from a type or norm .
secondary_definitions: ( genetics ) A different sequence of a gene ( locus ).
( programming ) A variable that can hold any of various unrelated data types .
( linguistics , lexicography ) One of a set of words or other linguistic forms that conveys the same meaning or serves the same function.
